PHAR 7247 - Pharmacy Practice Skills Laboratory – 7
This integrated course covers normal functioning and diseases of the
pulmonary system. Students will learn proper use of therapeutic devices,
develop treatment plan, select the appropriate assessments for
medication therapy management (MTM), and counsel patients with
pulmonary diseases. Diseases covered will include, asthma, COPD,
respiratory infections, cystic fibrosis, restrictive lung diseases and
pulmonary hypertension. In addition, students will learn treatment
approaches for special patient populations and how to determine
adjustments that may need to be made to care plans such as referrals.
Prerequisite: PHAR 7606, PHAR 7246. Corequisite: PHAR 7507.
